And if there is no proof on this point, then, by the common Laws of Nations, the thing is to be adjudged to the nation itself, provided it be taken in war. For from what we have said, it appears that the assertion of Quintilian is not exactly true, pleading for the Theban53 that in a matter which can be brought into a court of justice, the right of war goes for nothing 3 and that which is taken by arms can only be kept by arms.
